

"" Patience, Perseverance and Consistency ""


Patience

“To lose patience is to lose the battle.” ...
“Patience is bitter, but its fruit is sweet.” ...
“Knowing trees, I understand the meaning of patience. ...
“Have patience with all things but first of all with yourself.” ...
“Patience is the road to wisdom.” ...


Perseverance

“It always seems impossible until it is done.”
“Success is not final, failure is not fatal: It is the courage to continue that counts.”
“A bend in the road is not the end of the road… unless you fail to make the turn.”
“Perseverance is not a long race; it is many short races one after the other.”
“Success is no accident. It is hard work, perseverance, learning, studying, sacrifice and most of all, love of what you are doing or learning to do.”



Consistency

“I pray to be like the ocean, with soft currents, maybe waves at time. More and more, I want the consistency rather than the highs and lows.”
“Getting an audience is hard. Sustaining an audience is hard. It demands a consistency of thought, of purpose and of action over a long period of time.”
“Consistency is found in that work whose whole and detail are suitable to the occasion. It arises from circumstance, custom and nature.”
“People like consistency. Whether it’s a store or a restaurant, they want to come in and see what you are famous for.”
“It’s very easy to make a viral video, but longevity and consistency, that’s hard.”
